title: For Sale:  (sale pending)Smith & Wesson 6906 Compact Carry Pistol + Extras + 100 rds
postcontent:
(SALE PENDING) I have for sale a 9mm 6906 compact pistol by Smith and Wesson. This gun was owned by a family member who was a LEO. This gun was his backup and was carried on his ankle for over a year. It wasnt fired as much as it was carried, but it was indeed carried and it shows holster wear on the right side only. It's not terrible but if you're wanting a show gun this is not it! This gun is for carrying and shooting and its a fine shooter! The aluminum frame and stainless slide provide very little recoil, even less since I have added a new recoil spring (less than 50 rounds ago). This gun just recently came back from Smith and Wesson from having it's ejector (was chipped) replaced as well as the extractor just for the heck of it. That's the luxury of having a 3rd generation Smith is a free warranty to have any work done on it. They even pay for shipping at no cost to you! And you are only out 2-3 weeks if that. This particular repair took 11 days to get back. 

This gun comes with 3 magazines (12 rd) 1 of which is brand new, never loaded, the other two I replaced the springs (at the same time I did the recoil spring). I kept the old springs just in case I'd ever need them. It also has a Hogue full grip added to it, I kept the original grips as well. It also comes with a Galco Ankle holster, OEM box and Manual.

2 boxes of 9mm Magtech ammo (100 rds total) are included in the price as well as a Plano Carrying Case (smaller than the Smith OEM one for easy transportation). 

These are getting harder and harder to find (not impossible), Many LEOs still carry this as their side are in New York City, and its a super reliable, accurate gun. This is an excellent carrier for personal protection. I am selling because I have a 9mm that carry and I am used to it, although this gun is fun as hell to shoot as it's sooo accurate I have to stick with what I'm used to as I dont need four 9mms

Emails with phone numbers will be given 1st priority.  It has been transfered into my name so I require a MN DL and a PTP/PTC to purchase. Thank you!
